
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "FAQ";
}

<div class="container-fluid my-5 py-5">
    <div class="container bg-white shadow-lg rounded-3 my-5 py-3">
        <div class="text-center pt-5 mb-5">
            <h1 class="text-center fw-bold mb-4">
                Frequent questions
            </h1>
            <p class="text-green fw-bold leading-relaxed xl:w-2/4 lg:w-3/4 mx-auto">
                What you need to know about Zoodex is here.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap">
            <div class="w-full lg:w-1/2 px-5 py-2">
                <details class="mb-4">
                    <summary class="fw-bold question-bg-green-light text-white rounded-3 py-2 px-4">
                        Do I need to register to use Zoodex?
                    </summary>

                    <span class="px-4 py-2 mt-5">
                        Yes, you need to have an account with us before you can start
                        to analyze reptiles using Zoodex. You can create your account <a href="@Url.Action("Register", "Access")" class="green-light-text text-decoration-none button-hover"> <strong>here</strong></a>
                        and then sign in to get started.
                    </span>
                </details>
                <details class="mb-4">
                    <summary class="fw-bold question-bg-green-light text-white rounded-3 py-2 px-4">
                        What kind of animals can be tested using Zoodex?
                    </summary>

                    <span class="px-4 py-2">
                        Currently Zoodex only allows the analysis of reptiles. From a little
                        lizard to the dreaded crocodile can be analyzed with Zoodex!
                    </span>
                </details>
                <details class="mb-4">
                    <summary class="fw-bold question-bg-green-light text-white rounded-3 py-2 px-4">
                        What kind of information will I get using Zoodex?
                    </summary>

                    <span class="px-4 py-2">
                        Zoodex provides information the following information about the species
                        identified such as species, gender, average size, average weight,
                        habitat among others.
                    </span>
                </details>
                <details class="mb-4">
                    <summary class="fw-bold question-bg-green-light text-white rounded-3 py-2 px-4">
                        How does Zoodex know which reptile is in my image?
                    </summary>

                    <span class="px-4 py-2">
                        Zoodex uses Artificial Intelligence algorithms that allow us to
                        know which is the reptile using only a picture.
                    </span>
                </details>
                <details class="mb-4">
                    <summary class="fw-bold question-bg-green-light text-white rounded-3 py-2 px-4">
                        Can I delete my account when I don't need to use Zoodex?
                    </summary>

                    <span class="px-4 py-2">
                        We would like you to stay with us longer, but if
                        you think it is better to delete your account you can always do it
                        accessing your profile and clicking on "Delete my account".
                    </span>
                </details>
                <details class="mb-4">
                    <summary class="fw-bold question-bg-green-light text-white rounded-3 py-2 px-4">
                        Where can I contact you if I have more questions?
                    </summary>

                    <span class="px-4 py-2">
                        If you have any additional questions, send an email to the team of
                        Zoodex at: <a href="mailto:proyecto.zoodex@gmail.com" class="green-light-text text-decoration-none button-hover">proyecto.zoodex@gmail.com</a>
                    </span>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

